STATE of North Carolina
v.
Tara Nicole LABINSKI. No. 60P08. Supreme Court of North Carolina. April 10, 2008. Leslie S. Robinson, Greenville, for Labinski. John W. Congleton, Assistant Attorney General, Clark. Everett, District Attorney, for State of NC. Prior report: ___ N.C.App. ___, 654 S.E.2d 740 .

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Defendant on the 15th day of February 2008 for Writ of Supersedeas of the judgment of the Court of Appeals, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the North Carolina Court of Appeals:

"Denied by order of the Court in conference, this the 10th day of April 2008."

Upon consideration of the petition filed on the 15th day of February 2008 by Defendant in this matter for discretionary review of the decision of the North Carolina Court of Appeals pursuant to G.S. 7A-31, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the North Carolina Court of Appeals:

"Denied by order of the Court in conference, this the 10th day of April 2008."
